          <p rend="indent(1)"><addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(4)">Dear Sir</p>
          <p rend="indent(5)">Having long<lb/> since desired to obtain the &#8220;Letters on Judaism and<lb/> Christianity by <persName>B. F. Dias</persName>&#8221; I was pleased to learn<lb/> that you <sic>purpose</sic> publishing the same.<lb/> The superior merit of these Letters should at once<lb/> procure for them&#44; more than the required numbers<lb/> of subscribers enabling you to accomplish so desirable<lb/> an object&#44; as they certainly furnish a most powerful<lb/> and complete refutation of the church of Christ&#44;<lb/> please consider me a subscriber for one volume<lb/> with my best wishes for your health and<lb/> prosperity&#44; I have the honor of</p>
          <p rend="indent(9)">subscribing myself</p>
          <p rend="indent(9)">your obedient Servant</p>
          <p rend="indent(9)"><persName role="author">H. Leon</persName></p>
          <p rend="indent(9)"><placeName>28 Dey St.</placeName></p>
			<p><placeName>New York</placeName> <date>February 27&#47;53</date></p>
          
        </body>
